When the code is render in xml format {{code:xml}}, it print out an extra ">" at the end of attribute when *xsl* attribute name is used. This is happened only when it is rendered in *xml* code block, we don't see this if the normal code block is being used.

Actual example:

{code:xml}

<xsl:template name="xsl:initial-template">
</xsl:template>

{code}

Expected Result :
{code}

<xsl:template name="xsl:initial-template">
</xsl:template>

{code}

h3. Additional Information
Even without the dash in the attribute name, it still carry the same behaviour.
{code:xml}
<xsl:template name="xsl:initialtemplate">
</xsl:template>
{code}

h3. Work Around:
Use {{code}} instead of {{code:xml}} . However, there is one drawback of using normal code block which is the xml attribute colour highlight is not shown anymore.

{code}
<xsl:template name="xsl:initial-template">
</xsl:template>
{code}

