Hi,

We noticed that when a user browses to a plugin servlet, and the user is not allowed to do so, the redirect to the login page goes wrong.

There are two things that seem to go wrong in our case..
Take this common piece of code for servlets:
{code}
if (!userManager.isAdmin(userManager.getRemoteUsername(req))) {
    loginPage.redirect(req, resp);
}
{code}
In our case, the user who's trying to access the servlet is jira administrator (not system administrator). So he should not be redirect, but this happens anyways. If I give him sys admin permissions, he doesn't get redirected.

Second is the redirecting part. We configured JIRA to use a different login mechanism and thus not the default JIRA login page. So in our seraph-config.xml there is a complete URL {{https://federatedlogin.example.com/?origin={originalurl\}}}. The user gets redirect to https://jira.example.comhttps//federatedlogin.example.com/?origin=
which can't be found of course..

This happens in the SeraphLoginUriProvider
{code}return new URI(applicationProperties.getBaseUrl(UrlMode.AUTO) + newUrl);{code}
The baseURL should not be appended if the loginURL already contains a valid URL.

*to reproduce*
- Set the seraph login.url to a full URL (in seraph-config.xml)
- Login with a user, which is JIRA administrator, but not a system administrator..
- Browse to the Atlassian Support Tools

